		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P class=MsoNormal align=left 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt 0.25in?>
<P class=MsoNormal align=left 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt 0.25in?><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:><namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"><SPAN **Zowie**?TEXT-DECORATION: none?></SPAN></SPAN></P><SPAN Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: mso-fareast-font-family: Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN Ignore? **Zowie**?mso-list:>1)<SPAN New ?Times 7pt **Zowie**?FONT: Roman??>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<STRONG> </STRONG></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:><STRONG>Manaburn </STRONG>- A wizard can currently spend their entire mana bar to do a little over 9k damage in 5 seconds - leaving the wizard completely helpless and out of mana afterwards. At the same time Ancient Strike of Chaos - our best fire-based nuke can crit for over 8k using less than 1 bubble of mana and taking 1 more second to cost. The damage cap on manaburn should be removed (with the exception of PvP), and it should be returned to its pre-nerf state.<BR><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated.</FONT></SPAN></SPAN>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal align=left 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0.5in; l0 -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list:><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:></SPAN>2) <STRONG>Pillar Spells</STRONG> - Wizards grew up quad-kiting for a living. It is an insult to the class and the game that we are forced to fight level 70 monsters in Plane of Fire with a level 51 spell (Pillar of Frost). This line of spells - which is quite possibly the most used by wizards - has not had a meaningful update since KUNARK. New pillar spells should do in the 1500-1800 damage range (which is a lower ratio in terms of pillar versus nuke than the kunark pillars were compared to sunstrike). Mana cost should be higher to compensate for increased dmg output, however it is crucial that cast time remain low as this is a KITING spell and if it can't be cast in under 4 seconds, it is of no use.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal align=left 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0.5in; l0 -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list:><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal align=left 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0.5in; l0 -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list:><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>3) <STRONG>Mana Regeneration</STRONG> - First: Raise the cap from mana regen received from buffs. Currently wizards are the only class which gets hurt by the limit. Second: Raise the worn mana regen (FT) cap from 15 to 25 to represent the better equipment available in PoP and GoD. </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal align=left 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0.5in; l0 -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list:><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal align=left 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0.5in; l0 -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list:><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>4) <STRONG>Strong Root</STRONG> – Shorten recast timer and make it so Greater Fetter doesn’t overwrite it.<BR><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:><SPAN red? **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>This is a new item, I am sending it along.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>I hope to have information with the next update in 2 weeks</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></P><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt 0.25in?>5)&nbsp; <STRONG>Add an AA that prevents leaving group mates behind for Teleport and Evacuate spells<BR></STRONG><BR><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:><SPAN red? **SMURF**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>This is a new item, I am sending it along.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>I hope to have information with the next update in 2 weeks</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></FONT></P></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt 0.25in?><BR>6) <STRONG>Concussion</STRONG> - Pretty much covers what was stated before. An improved concussion for wizards would be nice, but the best way to handle the poor state of agro control for wizards is through AA's not new spells in my opinion.<BR><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:>Currently being discussed</SPAN></FONT></P><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt 0.25in?><BR></FONT>7)<STRONG> Lures</STRONG> - I often wonder if the "lures" we received in PoP were supposed to be a joke. In Kunark, Sunstrike did 1615 damage and Lure of Ice did 825 damage - about 2:1. Now wizards are using nukes that do 3000 damage, yet the best lure we have is Lure of Ro - 1070 damage. To keep lures in line with our major nuking spells they should do 1500 damage.<BR><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:>Currently being discussed</SPAN><BR>8) Rain spells - The primary problem here is resists and mezzes. You can't use a rain spell in a group because you will break mezzes. You can't root a mob and cast a rain spell because it will break the root. I'd refer you to the <A href="http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?t=17412&amp;highlight=rain" target=_blank><SPAN class=Hyperlink1><FONT color=#ffff00>Discussion Thread</FONT></SPAN></A><FONT color=#ffff00> </FONT>on Graffe's for more information.<BR><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></P><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt 0.25in?><BR>9) <STRONG>GoD Familiars</STRONG> - I couldn't wait when I heard we were getting new familiars in GoD. This changed when I found out we would be spending 45 AAs for 3 familiars that were all WORSE than the one we previously bought in PoP. Issues: The damage focus does not stack with bard song - it should or else there is no point for the familiar any time there is a bard on a raid or in a group. There is no mana regen on familiars - This was the number one perk from using allegiant familiar. There are no resists on the GoD familiars. At the least it should have resists for its resist. Allegiant Familiar had +30 to all resists. Ro's Familiar should be +75 Fire resist and +0 the others. <BR><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt 0.25in?><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:></SPAN><BR>10) <STRONG>Mana robe effects</STRONG> - Nobody is saying bring back the manastone. It is clear that doing so would bring serious class balance issues into question - namely the infinite stream of mana as long as you have a healer nearby. However, given that the mana regen caps have not be raised in aeons, the ability to convert hit points to mana is crucial for any wizard who wants to maintain a sustained level of damage output. Consider putting in an AA or long recast (like harvest) spell which converts 800 hitpoints into 400 mana. Additionally consider adding new items to the game that have similar effects of the mana robe.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt 0.25in?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN><B **Zowie**?mso-bidi-font-weight: normal?><U><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></U></B></P>
