		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT size=2>Wizard - <namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><FONT size=2><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:>1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manaburn - A wizard can currently spend their entire mana bar to do a little over 9k damage in 5 seconds - leaving the wizard completely helpless and out of mana afterwards. At the same time Ancient Strike of Chaos - our best fire-based nuke can crit for over 8k using less than 1 bubble of mana and taking 1 more second to cost. The damage cap on manaburn should be removed (with the exception of PvP), and it should be returned to its pre-nerf state.<BR></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated.</FONT></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:>Dev notes – Ideas have been floated around on how to fix the issues with Manaburn, the hope is to implement those before the Omens of War launch.</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:></SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT size=2>2) Pillar Spells - Wizards grew up quad-kiting for a living. It is an insult to the class and the game that we are forced to fight level 70 monsters in Plane of Fire with a level 51 spell (Pillar of Frost). This line of spells - which is quite possibly the most used by wizards - has not had a meaningful update since KUNARK. New pillar spells should do in the 1500-1800 damage range (which is a lower ratio in terms of pillar versus nuke than the kunark pillars were compared to sunstrike). Mana cost should be higher to compensate for increased dmg output, however it is crucial that cast time remain low as this is a KITING spell and if it can't be cast in under 4 seconds, it is of no use.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:>Currently being discussed</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:></SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT size=2>3) Mana Regeneration - First: Raise the cap from mana regen received from buffs. Currently wizards are the only class which gets hurt by the limit. Second: Raise the worn mana regen (FT) cap from 15 to 25 to represent the better equipment available in PoP and GoD. </FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:>Dev notes – “</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: red; Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:>To my knowledge, there is no cap for mana regen from buffs. The FT cap will be going up via AAs in Omens, but not much.”</SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: red; Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000 size=2>Ashlanne notes – If the Community believes there is a cap can I get that information?<SPAN yes? **Oompa-Loompa**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>Otherwise I am going to change this to </FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; COLOR: 9pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>(<SPAN **Zowie**?COLOR: red?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;>This is something that will be considered in future expansions</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: **Zowie**?COLOR: red; Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial?>.)</SPAN></SPAN></FONT><SPAN **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><FONT size=2><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:>4) Strong Root – Shorten recast timer and make it so Greater Fetter doesn’t overwrite it.<BR></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT size=2>5) </FONT><FONT size=2><B>Add an AA that prevents leaving group mates behind for Teleport and Evacuate spells<BR></B><BR></FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><BR><FONT size=2>6) Concussion - Pretty much covers what was stated before. An improved concussion for wizards would be nice, but the best way to handle the poor state of agro control for wizards is through AA's not new spells in my opinion.<BR></FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000 size=2>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><BR><FONT size=2>7) Lures - I often wonder if the "lures" we received in PoP were supposed to be a joke. In Kunark, Sunstrike did 1615 damage and Lure of Ice did 825 damage - about 2:1. Now wizards are using nukes that do 3000 damage, yet the best lure we have is Lure of Ro - 1070 damage. To keep lures in line with our major nuking spells they should do 1500 damage.<BR></FONT></SPAN><FONT size=2><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT><BR></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:>8) Rain spells - The primary problem here is resists and mezzes. You can't use a rain spell in a group because you will break mezzes. You can't root a mob and cast a rain spell because it will break the root. I'd refer you to the <A href="http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?t=17412&amp;highlight=rain" target=_blank><SPAN **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: yellow?><FONT color=#ffcc33>Discussion Thread</FONT></SPAN></A></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR: yellow;> </SPAN></FONT><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT size=2>on Graffe's for more information.<BR></FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT><BR></FONT></SPAN><FONT size=2><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:>9) GoD Familiars - I couldn't wait when I heard we were getting new familiars in GoD. This changed when I found out we would be spending 45 AAs for 3 familiars that were all WORSE than the one we previously bought in PoP. Issues: The damage focus does not stack with bard song - it should or else there is no point for the familiar any time there is a bard on a raid or in a group. There is no mana regen on familiars - This was the number one perk from using allegiant familiar. There are no resists on the GoD familiars. At the least it should have resists for its resist. Allegiant Familiar had +30 to all resists. Ro's Familiar should be +75 Fire resist and +0 the others. <BR></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></SPAN></FONT><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><BR><FONT size=2>10) Mana robe effects - Nobody is saying bring back the manastone. It is clear that doing so would bring serious class balance issues into question - namely the infinite stream of mana as long as you have a healer nearby. However, given that the mana regen caps have not be raised in aeons, the ability to convert hit points to mana is crucial for any wizard who wants to maintain a sustained level of damage output. Consider putting in an AA or long recast (like harvest) spell which converts 800 hitpoints into 400 mana. Additionally consider adding new items to the game that have similar effects of the mana robe.</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><FONT size=2><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? red; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:>Currently being discussed</SPAN><B><U><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:></SPAN></U></B></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-FAMILY:><FONT size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal align=left **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt 0.25in?><FONT color=#66ccff>U<SPAN 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>pdated list 8/06/04</SPAN></FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></P>
