			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=2757#M2757">17</a> of 24
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 6132 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff00ff><STRONG>Wizard</STRONG> - <FONT size=2><STRONG>List Update scheduled for&nbsp;04/01/05</STRONG></FONT></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1) <STRONG>Short to Medium term damage -</STRONG> <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>This will most likely be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.&nbsp; Some changes have been made to your damage dealing spells on Test Server.</STRONG></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>Wizards are currently falling further and further behind in these areas, areas that they should actually excel given the major limitations on their damage potential. In reality, any class that isn't mana based should not even come close, and yet, many do, often exceeding the class by more than a minor amount. This is just exacerbated by the current trend of making fights last longer again, which actually only hurts classes that have built in limits on their damage, Wizards being the one that is probably the most affected by it. And this is without even taking into account mob abilities that affect casters to an even greater extent (high resists, mana drains, and even total immunities to spell damage).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>2) Long term damage</STRONG> -&nbsp;&nbsp;<FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being discussed, This will most likely be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.&nbsp; Some changes have been made to your damage dealing spells on Test Server.</STRONG></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>While Wizards tend to be be more focused on short term damage, they do suffer a lot when it comes to long term damage in groups because their damage is all mana based. This tends to mean that classes that come very close to or even exceed them in short term damage just destroy them when it comes to long term damage because they have no such limitations. Some ideas may be help with mana regen in places where this is a problem, or an extended line of spells that address this problem (lower dps, but higher efficiency).<BR></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>3) Manaburn - <FONT color=#ff0000>Changes to manaburn will come with part #1 of the Class Re-Envision process.</FONT><BR></STRONG>A Wizard can currently spend their entire mana bar to do a little over 9k damage in 5 seconds - leaving the wizard completely helpless and out of mana afterwards. At the same time Ancient Strike of Chaos - our best fire-based nuke can crit for over 8k using less than 1 bubble of mana and taking 1 more second to cost. The damage cap on manaburn should be removed (with the exception of PvP), and it should be returned to its pre-nerf state.<BR>&nbsp;<BR><STRONG>4) Aggro problems - <FONT color=#ff0000>Changes to the way aggro is gained through spells is being considered with part #1 of the Class Re-Envision Process.</FONT></STRONG><BR>As spell damage goes up, aggro also increases. And so does mob damage output. So the penalty for gaining aggro for any reason can often be almost instant death. Currently Maelin's legs are the only real method used for aggro control at the high end, and they put Wizards roughly where they should be in terms of overall damage, while allowing some capability to maybe escape death when the MT goes down. But as spell damage goes up, they will become more of a limiter on how much dps rises because aggro is still going to be the main limitation, which would essentially leave Wizards in the same spot (concussion is a fixed amount, it doesn't scale in the manner that Evade can if you get too high on the list and there is no version of Wizard 'Escape'). Going back to spell based Concussion doesn't really solve the overall problem, it just increases the chance that Wizards will die when the MT does while likely lowering overall dps.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><BR><STRONG>5) Resists - <FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>Wizards were supposed to be able to have an innately better chance of landing spells than any other class because all of our damage is based on mana, and resists affect both our short term and our long term damage (a resist, unlike a miss, is not something you can recover in the long term because it has a cost, the mana you used is already spent and did nothing but increase your aggro). When the resist change went in, this was basically handled under the new system by giving some of our spells a resist modifier, but not all. Magic spells, for example, do not share the resist modifier that fire and cold spells get. Also, as you level and go further into the high end of an expansion, the resists also tend to get worse. It would be nice to Look into whether or not the resist modifiers on the current spells are where they should be and seeing if the penalty for being resisted is perhaps too high as well. Magic based spells should get the resist adjustment the other spells have as well.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>6) Low/Mid Level Wizard Damage - <FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed, This will most likely be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.</FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>While melee have every expansion gained numerous new weapons available at the lower levels that are markedly better in dealing out damage, casters have essentially remained static, casting the same spells they have always cast since the beginning. Slightly larger mana pools and minimally better mana regen hasn't really helped this too much. This has led to a situation where they are outdamaged in both the long and short term by melee, especially Wizards because there is no pet damage to fall back on (which can be helped with newer 'trash' weapons or pet only weapons in much the same way as melee). Suggestion would be to perhaps revisit the spell lines of lower and midrange casters to give some updated spells, perhaps available off harder encounters of those levels to alleviate the situation.<BR>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>7) AA Issues</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>- Frenzied Devastation -While the last change upped the efficiency of the ability, it still seems like it loses efficiency on average at the base level. If you add in the fact that focus items aren't even considered in the equation, this ability definitely loses comparative efficiency, the better your focus items, the worse off you are. It would actually be nice if this actually gained slightly in efficiency as you got more levels simply because it currently on par with similar melee abilities to gain DPS which don't seem to have the same problems. <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being discussed</STRONG></FONT><BR>- Ward of Destruction - The damage done by the spell even at the max level is extremely low and the static nature of it also makes the damage output even less reliable.&nbsp; <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated.&nbsp; Rashere is currently looking into ways to make this AA more useful. <BR></FONT></STRONG>- Familiars - Should be more of a reason to use the GoD familiars, currently they are only used on short fights where you don't have a Bard because of the lack of mana regen and resists as well as the fact they are only dedicated to one resist type. It would also be nice if the other AA familiars were changed to the same 1 minute recast and instant cast as these. - <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>Currently being discussed</STRONG> </FONT><BR>- Strong Root – Shorten recast timer and make it so Greater Fetter doesn’t overwrite it. - <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>8) Mana Pool Buffs - <FONT color=#ff0000>The Mana cap is being removed with the Class Re-Envision process</FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>There is currently a cap on mana received via buffs at 750. At the moment, this cap mainly affects Wizards because of the additional mana provided by familiars. In OoW it will likely apply to other classes as well because of the new Clairvoyance spell adding 400 mana. Is there any real reason for this to be capped?<BR>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>9) Rain spells - <FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed, The inherent resist rate from rain spells is being removed as part of the Class Re-Envision Process</FONT></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>The primary problem here is resists and mezzes. You can't use a rain spell in a group because you will break mezzes. You can't root a mob and cast a rain spell because it will break the root. Rain spell also seem to have a built in 20% resist rate which seems rather excessive.<BR>&nbsp;<BR></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>10) Teleporting issues - <FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></STRONG><BR></DIV>
<UL>
<LI>Add an AA that prevents leaving group mates behind for Teleport and Evacuate spells<FONT color=#ff0000> </FONT>
<LI>The base time and mana cost on some port spells seems rather excessive (Knowledge Portal as a level 39 spell for 600 mana and 24 seconds being one of these, porting to Hate, a higher level spell, is only 300 mana and 10 seconds). 
<LI>Some method of removing the requirement for fragments being used for translocates. Removing the reagant requirements from Hate/Sky with the same method would also be appreciated. 
<LI>More useful locations that aren't 1 zone or less away from PoK. <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Community suggestions on new port locations - </FONT></STRONG><BR>Riftseekers<BR>Western Wastes<BR>Plane of Traquility<BR>Chardok – Near Chardock B<BR>Dragon Necropolis<BR>Dranik’s Scar<BR>Timorous Deep<BR>Crypt of Nadox<BR>Lake Rathe - <FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>With the announcement of a portal to the Arean being added to the Plane of Knowledge we may want to remove this location.</STRONG></FONT><BR>Umbral Plains – Near the Maiden’s Eye zone line<BR>Ocean of Tears 
<LI>Decession - Make Decession a bit more 'raid' friendly by either allowing it to work on anyone in a raid or giving a short timer TL box when cast on someone outside of your group (it needs to retain the no box ability inside your group in either case). 
<LI>Create Gate, Portal, and Translocate spells for all of the evacuation locations.</LI></UL></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							*************************************************<br>Ashlanne Barefoot<br>Community Relations Coordinator<br>Norrath, where I kick off my shoes and run in bare feet.<br><b><a href="http://stationforums.station.sony.com/communitysoe/ "><font color="red">Check out the Station Forums!</font></a>
							</div>
								
